rComments: Uses great analogies and comparisons that help students better understand the content in a way they'll remember. She was a little bit scattered at times, but in fairness it was partly because this was her first time teaching this course in several years, so she did great under the circumstances. Lectures were useful and interactive as well.

Prof. Jockush is an excellent teacher.  She is always prepared and delivers well-organized lectures.  She is very good at addressing student questions and clearing up any confusion about the material being covered.
Excellent prof; explains concepts very clearly and gives many examples to help students understand the concepts. Her term-test was fair and easy.
